(202, 1, '2023-01-01 05:44:37', '2023-01-01 05:44:37', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nail art is everywhere these days—a trend that once used to be the calling card of mall rats and music videos is now worn by a multitude of celebrities on the red carpet, as well as down the runways at Fashion Week, not just in New York, but also in Milan and Paris. Beauty companies have caught on too, just judging by the variety of at-home kits, special effects polishes, and Minx-like decals that have launched recently, allowing you to try out the trend without heading to the salon. In addition, nail design-dedicated blogs have been popping up at a rate that rivals the number of street style sites out there (hard to imagine right?), showing off the best nail art creations one can find on the internet. It\'s hard to believe that there are people out there who have enough hand-eye coordination to create an intricate winter wonderland scene on one little fingernail (I mean, I can barely paint a smiley face on my thumb let alone a snowman with a pipe), but they do, and you can see their amazing artwork if you know where to look. Here, are my top sites to visit for a little manicure inspiration, or simply to marvel at during a mid-afternoon break from the daily grind.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Nail Ideas: Top Nail Art Blogs to Check Out Now |', 'Nail art is everywhere these days—a trend that once used to be the calling card of mall rats and music videos is now worn by a multitude of celebrities on the red carpet, as well as down the runways at Fashion Week', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nail-ideas-top-nail-art-blogs-to-check-out-now', '', '', '2023-01-01 05:44:37', '2023-01-01 05:44:37', '', 0, 'http://localhost/my_wp/?p=202', 0, 'post', '', 0),
